Communicated by:
ProMED

[With the resumption of cruises (caveat emptor), it is not surprising that outbreaks in the closed environment of transoceanic cruise ships are beginning to occur. COVID-19 and norovirus are the 2 most recognized outbreaks on the ships but, as seen in the See Also list below, many other outbreaks can occur. Although the details in the CDC report above cite _Vibrio_ (likely _V. parahaemolyticus_ from raw shellfish_) and _E. coli_ (likely not the enterohemorrhagic type) as the pathogens involved, both are likely foodborne. - Mod.LL

